Tuggie, <br>
32 Mage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubelhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belhaven</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 4:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1071.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Torch of Alna, and Stein of Ulissa Quest assistance requ</span><hr size=1> nope - In najena, just the magicians drop the focus items.   However, it is ANY magician.  Downstairs (near the ogres) there are a couple of Magician spawn points (one can spawn a Named, though).  Back near Najena's hole, there can be some Goblin magicians as well.  <br>
<br>
If you're soloing, you can probably take the main 4 magicians and might be able to get to some of the goblins.  If you're grouped - split off a few to handle the ones downstairs and then pull all the top-floor ones to the rest of your party to kill them.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you're tired of Najena, the crocodiles that used to infest Cazic Thule can now be found in Feerott forest.  They too can drop the focus items.  Watch out for bouncers.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Belhaven<BR>
